Your taste skews firmly toward the 2000s and 2010s, a period when artists in the post-rock, ambient, and electronic spaces were finding sophisticated new ways to merge those influences. You appreciate accessibility but on your own terms — you liked Arlo Parks more than you expected precisely because it surprised you, while Maggie Rogers felt too straightforwardly pop. This suggests you''re not opposed to melody or even commercial polish, but you need a sense of craft and texture underneath it. You''re an engaged, curious listener who is actively expanding your palette: your jazz journey from Miles Davis toward Coltrane shows someone willing to push into unfamiliar territory incrementally, at their own pace.

